WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.800 --> 00:00:08.300 position:81%
Welcome to the 4th Generation iPod Take Apart Guide!

00:00:10.400 --> 00:00:15.300 position:97%
To begin, grab a flat head screwdriver or an iPod opening tool

00:00:15.900 --> 00:00:19.900 position:94%
and gently pry along the edge of the topcase and bottom pan.

00:00:20.200 --> 00:00:24.000 position:91%
Lifting the top section of the iPod out of the bottom pan.

00:00:53.800 --> 00:00:55.500
Now flip the iPod over.

00:00:56.500 --> 00:01:00.300 position:98%
And lifting from the bottom to the top, flip the bottom pan over.

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:05.100 position:73%
And disconnect the ribbon from the Logic Board.

00:01:29.100 --> 00:01:32.000 position:75%
Once thats complete, now lift the hard drive up.

00:01:32.400 --> 00:01:37.500 position:92%
And remove the black tape covering the hard drive connector

00:01:37.700 --> 00:01:39.100
to the Logic Board.

00:01:43.700 --> 00:01:44.200
Once thats complete,

00:01:44.600 --> 00:01:48.600 position:97%
now lift the lock bar that is holding the ribbon cable in place,

00:01:48.900 --> 00:01:53.000 position:98%
and gently remove the ribbon cable from the ribbon cable connector.

00:01:56.400 --> 00:01:57.900
Now lock the bar back in place.

00:02:02.700 --> 00:02:04.000
Once that is complete,

00:02:04.200 --> 00:02:08.100 position:73%
now remove the two cables from the Logic Board.

00:02:43.300 --> 00:02:44.300
Once that is complete,

00:02:44.800 --> 00:02:46.200
now grab your T6 screwdriver,

00:02:46.400 --> 00:02:50.300 position:78%
and remove the six T6 screws from the Logic Board.

00:03:25.800 --> 00:03:29.200 position:72%
Once that is complete, now grab your flat tool

00:03:29.400 --> 00:03:34.500 position:89%
and gently pry the Logic Board up and over onto its side.

00:03:45.600 --> 00:03:48.400 position:84%
Now you can remove the LCD cable from the Logic Board.

00:04:21.600 --> 00:04:24.600 position:69%
Now simply lift the LCD out of the top case.

00:04:29.300 --> 00:04:30.400
And to remove the battery,

00:04:30.800 --> 00:04:32.700
it is held on by adhesive tape.

00:04:33.900 --> 00:04:37.100
Gently pry this up and free.

00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:52.300
To remove the click wheel,

00:04:52.700 --> 00:04:56.600 position:88%
simply apply pressure to the outside of the click wheel.

00:04:59.400 --> 00:05:01.300 position:59%
This is only held on by adhesive tape.

00:05:11.500 --> 00:05:14.000 position:84%
To remove the headphone jack and hold button assembly,

00:05:15.400 --> 00:05:16.700
grab a phillips head screwdriver

00:05:16.900 --> 00:05:19.300 position:63%
and remove the two phillips head screws.

00:05:45.600 --> 00:05:49.200
And now the two Torx T6 screws.

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:10.500 position:61%
Now remove the headphone jack assembly.

00:06:14.900 --> 00:06:16.900 position:69%
And now remove the last phillips head screw.

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:23.000 position:80%
Once this is complete this simply lifts up and out.

